ONE of the top-grossing Nollywood movies of 2021, ‘April Showers’ has made its debut on the global streaming platform Amazon Prime. The film joins a few other Nigerian-produced films on the movies streaming platform after enjoying over 90 days in the cinemas.   Why I disguise as mad man to bless people, by De General     Blood Sisters: Deyemi Okanlawon, Gabriel Afolayan, Genevova…     Blossom Chukwujekwu’s ex-wife laughs off new marriage   Sandra Bremaud, the film producer, shared the news on her social media page. Bremaud said: “This actually made me feel proud of myself, my team, the entire cast and crew of April Showers as it is obvious we made an international standard movie which pricked the interest of Amazon Prime; I am delighted to say that April showers is now streaming and people from all around the world can see what we made”. Written by Pacass Adebayo, the movie which was released in October 2021 stars big names like Lilian Esoro, Eyinna Nwigwe, Kunle Remi, Pere Egbi, and Anthony Monjaro among others.